author: 13abc
title: Great Lakes storm creates wind and gale warnings
text:
MARQUETTE, MI (13abc Action News) â€“ The first strong fall storm system is moving through the northern Great Lakes. The storm is bringing a 20-degree cool down, strong winds, and high waves.
The National Weather Service has issued a Gale Warning for eastern Lake Superior and northern Lake Huron. Waves are expected to reach 10 to 15 feet high. Waves on western Lake Erie are expected to be around 2 to 4 feet.
The Great Lakes becomes a hot spot for strong storm systems in the middle of October to the middle of November each year. As storm systems move into the Great Lakes, they can intensify due to the relatively warm water of the Great Lakes. Lake-effect rain and snow also become common behind cold fronts.
